HEADWORD: firedamp
<hw>firedamp</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a mixture of gases (mostly methane)
that forms in coal mines and becomes explosive when mixed with air. It
is a source of serious hazard in coal mining operations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

